The paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The reallocation aspect of the problem also suggests that game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.LG) may be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the fact that the paper proposes an algorithm for maintaining a valid schedule suggests that systems and control (cs.SY) may also be a relevant sub-category.
